SUMMARY:🔥 US BEA: Personal Income and Outlays\, October and November 2
 025
DESCRIPTION:Source: US BEA\nImpact: high\nSource: US BEA\nImpact: high\nS
 ource: US BEA\nImpact: high\nSource: US BEA\nImpact: high\nSource: US BE
 A\nImpact: high\nSource: US BEA\nImpact: high\nwww.bea.gov\n\nExplainer:
 \n• What it is: Core PCE Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices
  paid by consumers for goods and services\, excluding food and energy.\n
 \n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bul
 lish for USD and bearish for bonds\, because it can increase expectation
 s of tighter Federal Reserve policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Core PCE i
 s one of the Federal Reserve's preferred inflation measures\, so it can 
 strongly influence interest-rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly
 \, usually released about four weeks after the month ends.\n\n• Notes:
  Core PCE differs from Core CPI because it uses a different basket and w
 eighting method. CPI often gets more immediate market attention\, but Co
 re PCE is very important for Fed policy.\n\n• Acronyms: PCE = Personal
  Consumption Expenditures\; CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial sour
 ce: https://www.bea.gov/news/schedule/ics/online-calendar-subscription.i
 cs\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Core PCE Price Index\n\n• Measures: 
