 fect: Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the local cu
 rrency and bearish for bonds\, because markets may price in higher inter
 est rates.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watched infla
 tion indicators because it can quickly shift central-bank rate expectati
 ons.\n\n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthl
 y indicator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI 
 removes volatile items such as food and energy to give a cleaner read on
  underlying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price In
