 or bonds\, because markets may price in higher interest rates.\n\n• Wh
 y traders care: CPI is one of the most watched inflation indicators beca
 use it can quickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n\n• Frequenc
 y: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indicator releases
  and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes volatile ite
 ms such as food and energy to give a cleaner read on underlying inflatio
 n pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial sou
 rce: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflati
 on/consumer-price-index-australia/apr-2026
