 s of tighter Federal Reserve policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Core PCE i
 s one of the Federal Reserve's preferred inflation measures\, so it can 
 strongly influence interest-rate expectations.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly
 \, usually released about four weeks after the month ends.\n\n• Notes:
  Core PCE differs from Core CPI because it uses a different basket and w
 eighting method. CPI often gets more immediate market attention\, but Co
 re PCE is very important for Fed policy.\n\n• Acronyms: PCE = Personal
