 s: Consumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the prices paid by co
 nsumers for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: 
 Higher-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the local currency
  and bearish for bonds\, because markets may price in higher interest ra
 tes.\n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watched inflation i
 ndicators because it can quickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n
 \n• Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indi
 cator releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI remove
 s volatile items such as food and energy to give a cleaner read on under
 lying inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n
