DESCRIPTION:Source: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nSource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nS
 ource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nSource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nSource: AU AB
 S\nImpact: high\nSource: AU ABS\nImpact: high\nOfficial ABS series page 
 release date. Time zone shown by ABS: AEST.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it i
 s: Producer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in prices received by pr
 oducers for goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-
 forecast PPI can be bullish for the local currency if traders expect pro
 ducer inflation to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why trader
 s care: PPI can provide an early signal of inflation pressure before it 
 reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Aus
 tralia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\, but i
 t can still matter when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acrony
 ms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.
 au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-indexes
 -australia\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n• Me
 asures: Change in prices received by producers for goods and services.\n
 \n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish for t
 he local currency if traders expect producer inflation to flow through t
 o consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an early 
 signal of inflation pressure before it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequen
 cy: Monthly in the US. Quarterly in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usua
 lly less market-moving than CPI\, but it can still matter when inflation
  is the main macro theme.\n\n• Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n
 \nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-index
 es-and-inflation/producer-price-indexes-australia\n\nExplainer:\n• Wha
