  by producers for goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher
 -than-forecast PPI can be bullish for the local currency if traders expe
 ct producer inflation to flow through to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why 
 traders care: PPI can provide an early signal of inflation pressure befo
 re it reaches consumers.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly in the US. Quarterly 
 in Australia.\n\n• Notes: PPI is usually less market-moving than CPI\,
  but it can still matter when inflation is the main macro theme.\n\n• 
 Acronyms: PPI = Producer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.ab
 s.gov.au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/producer-price-i
 ndexes-australia\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Producer Price Index\n\n
 • Measures: Change in prices received by producers for goods and servi
 ces.\n\n• Usual market effect: Higher-than-forecast PPI can be bullish
  for the local currency if traders expect producer inflation to flow thr
 ough to consumer inflation.\n\n• Why traders care: PPI can provide an 
