 ositive for consumers but can also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• A
 cronyms: WPI = Wage Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov
 .au/statistics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/wage-price-index-aust
 ralia\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Wage Price Index / Average Earnings
 \n\n• Measures: Change in wages and earnings.\n\n• Usual market effe
 ct: Higher-than-forecast wage growth can be bullish for the local curren
 cy if traders expect stronger inflation pressure and tighter central-ban
 k policy.\n\n• Why traders care: Wage growth can feed into inflation a
 nd is closely watched by central banks.\n\n• Frequency: Monthly or qua
 rterly depending on release.\n\n• Notes: Strong wages can be positive 
 for consumers but can also increase inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms:
  WPI = Wage Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/stat
 istics/economy/price-indexes-and-inflation/wage-price-index-australia
