 arish for bonds. More dovish-than-expected guidance is usually bearish f
 or the currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders care: Central-
 bank decisions directly affect interest rates\, currency valuation\, bon
 d yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Scheduled several t
 imes per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often reacts not only to the rat
 e decision\, but also to the statement\, forecasts\, press conference an
 d tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Committee\; RBA = Re
