  CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.abs.gov.au/
 release-calendar/future-releases/202610\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: C
 onsumer Price Index\n\n• Measures: Change in the prices paid by consum
 ers for a basket of goods and services.\n\n• Usual market effect: High
 er-than-forecast inflation is usually bullish for the local currency and
  bearish for bonds\, because markets may price in higher interest rates.
 \n\n• Why traders care: CPI is one of the most watched inflation indic
 ators because it can quickly shift central-bank rate expectations.\n\n
 • Frequency: US CPI is monthly. Australian CPI has both monthly indica
 tor releases and quarterly CPI releases.\n\n• Notes: Core CPI removes 
 volatile items such as food and energy to give a cleaner read on underly
 ing inflation pressure.\n\n• Acronyms: CPI = Consumer Price Index.\n\n
 Official source: https://www.abs.gov.au/release-calendar/future-releases
 /202610
