SUMMARY:🔥 US Fed: FOMC Interest Rate Decision
DESCRIPTION:Source: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nS
 ource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fe
 d\nImpact: high\nSource: US Fed\nImpact: high\nOfficial Federal Reserve 
 monthly calendar FOMC meeting entry.\n\nExplainer:\n• What it is: Cent
 ral Bank Rate Decision\n\n• Measures: Interest-rate decision\, policy 
 statement and guidance from the central bank.\n\n• Usual market effect
 : More hawkish-than-expected guidance is usually bullish for the local c
 urrency and bearish for bonds. More dovish-than-expected guidance is usu
 ally bearish for the currency and bullish for bonds.\n\n• Why traders 
 care: Central-bank decisions directly affect interest rates\, currency v
 aluation\, bond yields and equity risk appetite.\n\n• Frequency: Sched
 uled several times per year.\n\n• Notes: The market often reacts not o
 nly to the rate decision\, but also to the statement\, forecasts\, press
  conference and tone.\n\n• Acronyms: FOMC = Federal Open Market Commit
 tee\; RBA = Reserve Bank of Australia.\n\nOfficial source: https://www.f
 ederalreserve.gov/newsevents/2026-december.htm\n\nExplainer:\n• What i
